>>CURTIS: Well, I mean, interest
rates were slashed back in--

00:18:15.975 --> 00:18:17.907 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: 2008.

00:18:17.907 --> 00:18:19.740 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: Yeah, when
Obama came into office.

00:18:19.740 --> 00:18:20.170 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:18:20.170 --> 00:18:21.350 align:middle line:90%
They were already before that.

00:18:21.350 --> 00:18:22.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And they
haven't gone up since.

00:18:22.330 --> 00:18:23.150 align:middle line:90%
>>CURTIS: No, they haven't.

00:18:23.150 --> 00:18:24.255 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Which is unprecedented.

00:18:24.255 --> 00:18:25.870 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: Well, it's
unprecedented in the United

00:18:25.870 --> 00:18:26.190 align:middle line:90%
States.

00:18:26.190 --> 00:18:27.523 align:middle line:90%
It's not unprecedented in Japan.

00:18:27.523 --> 00:18:30.200 align:middle line:84%
Japan has had zero-- they have
negative interest rates right

00:18:30.200 --> 00:18:32.620 align:middle line:84%
now, where you actually get
incentive for companies, where

00:18:32.620 --> 00:18:35.372 align:middle line:84%
they're buying
below par on money,

00:18:35.372 --> 00:18:37.080 align:middle line:84%
where the government
is subsidizing them.

00:18:37.080 --> 00:18:38.370 align:middle line:90%
They could do that too.

00:18:38.370 --> 00:18:41.120 align:middle line:84%
Federal Reserve Board could
actually subsidize banks.

00:18:41.120 --> 00:18:43.750 align:middle line:84%
Listen, there's
no limit, George,

00:18:43.750 --> 00:18:46.290 align:middle line:84%
to how much money the Federal
Reserve Board can print.

00:18:46.290 --> 00:18:48.290 align:middle line:84%
If you looked at their
website and they told you

00:18:48.290 --> 00:18:51.130 align:middle line:84%
in 2008, 2009, when
they were trying

00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:53.060 align:middle line:84%
to piece this economy
back together,

00:18:53.060 --> 00:18:55.450 align:middle line:84%
how much money the Federal
Reserve Board printed,

00:18:55.450 --> 00:18:58.590 align:middle line:84%
on their website they said
they printed $6 trillion.

00:18:58.590 --> 00:18:59.939 align:middle line:90%
We know that in order--

00:18:59.939 --> 00:19:00.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Just printed it.

00:19:00.980 --> 00:19:02.479 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: No, but
I mean $6 trillion

00:19:02.479 --> 00:19:03.690 align:middle line:90%
was a drop in the bucket.

00:19:03.690 --> 00:19:08.190 align:middle line:84%
They printed actually,
and there's $24 trillion

00:19:08.190 --> 00:19:10.360 align:middle line:84%
that is completely
unaccounted for.

00:19:10.360 --> 00:19:12.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What you
mean unaccounted for?

00:19:12.620 --> 00:19:14.890 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: It's not on their
books, the Federal Reserve

00:19:14.890 --> 00:19:15.270 align:middle line:90%
Board.

00:19:15.270 --> 00:19:16.370 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But it's in
the system somewhere?

00:19:16.370 --> 00:19:17.578 align:middle line:90%
>>CURTIS: It's in the system.

00:19:17.578 --> 00:19:19.030 align:middle line:90%
It's in JP Morgan's hands.

00:19:19.030 --> 00:19:20.370 align:middle line:90%
It's in Wells Fargo's hands.

00:19:20.370 --> 00:19:21.760 align:middle line:90%
It's an AIG's hands.

00:19:21.760 --> 00:19:23.790 align:middle line:84%
All the companies--
it's in General Motors--

00:19:23.790 --> 00:19:24.095 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Bank of America.

00:19:24.095 --> 00:19:26.020 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: Bank of
America-- all the companies

00:19:26.020 --> 00:19:26.895 align:middle line:90%
that were bailed out.

00:19:26.895 --> 00:19:30.530 align:middle line:84%
It took close to $30 trillion
to bail out the country

00:19:30.530 --> 00:19:32.300 align:middle line:90%
in 2008, not the $6 trillion.

00:19:32.300 --> 00:19:35.680 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Had they not done
that, had they simply said,

00:19:35.680 --> 00:19:39.980 align:middle line:84%
let it fail, let it collapse,
what would have happened,

00:19:39.980 --> 00:19:41.220 align:middle line:90%
in your opinion?

00:19:41.220 --> 00:19:44.500 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: I think you would
have seen runs on the banks

00:19:44.500 --> 00:19:45.560 align:middle line:90%
everywhere.

00:19:45.560 --> 00:19:51.510 align:middle line:84%
I think you would have
seen the 1929 repeat.

00:19:51.510 --> 00:19:52.900 align:middle line:90%
History would repeat itself.

00:19:52.900 --> 00:19:55.130 align:middle line:84%
You'd have an instant
replay of people

00:19:55.130 --> 00:19:58.610 align:middle line:84%
rushing to their financial
institutions with nothing left.

00:19:58.610 --> 00:20:01.020 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
risk that you had.

00:20:01.020 --> 00:20:03.810 align:middle line:84%
The idea that somehow,
let 'em all go under,

00:20:03.810 --> 00:20:06.530 align:middle line:84%
let all the big boys--
let 'em all fail,

00:20:06.530 --> 00:20:10.330 align:middle line:84%
the big manufacturers,
Detroit, let the banks fail,

00:20:10.330 --> 00:20:14.700 align:middle line:84%
you would have found a disaster
of far worse proportions

00:20:14.700 --> 00:20:17.540 align:middle line:84%
than you saw in '29 and
through the Great Depression.

00:20:17.540 --> 00:20:20.330 align:middle line:84%
Look, they called the last
recession the Great Recession.

00:20:20.330 --> 00:20:23.370 align:middle line:84%
It could very easily morphed
without this Federal Reserve

00:20:23.370 --> 00:20:27.590 align:middle line:84%
intervention into
something far more atomic

00:20:27.590 --> 00:20:29.750 align:middle line:90%
and catastrophic and nuclear.

00:20:29.750 --> 00:20:32.820 align:middle line:90%


00:20:32.820 --> 00:20:37.430 align:middle line:84%
Had they not provided the
liquidity to the banks,

00:20:37.430 --> 00:20:40.684 align:middle line:84%
I think that's what would
have happened in 2008, 2009.

00:20:40.684 --> 00:20:41.850 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's all we need.

00:20:41.850 --> 00:20:45.860 align:middle line:84%
Now, most of you probably
don't remember the recession

00:20:45.860 --> 00:20:49.530 align:middle line:84%
from way gone back, the
Great Depression, I guess,

00:20:49.530 --> 00:20:51.200 align:middle line:90%
as we would call it.

00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:52.590 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't even born then.

00:20:52.590 --> 00:20:54.400 align:middle line:84%
John, I don't think
you were either.

00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:55.530 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: No, but I
know a lot of people

00:20:55.530 --> 00:20:56.446 align:middle line:90%
that lived through it.

00:20:56.446 --> 00:21:01.100 align:middle line:84%
And it's been passed to me that
when people have no money--

00:21:01.100 --> 00:21:03.750 align:middle line:84%
look, there's people living
on the fringe right now.

00:21:03.750 --> 00:21:06.590 align:middle line:84%
Let's not for a second
think that this economy,

00:21:06.590 --> 00:21:09.590 align:middle line:84%
this economic recovery
we have is really

00:21:09.590 --> 00:21:11.120 align:middle line:90%
widespread for a lot of people.

00:21:11.120 --> 00:21:12.030 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's not.

00:21:12.030 --> 00:21:14.280 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: There are people--
this is where I'm headed.

00:21:14.280 --> 00:21:18.200 align:middle line:84%
The job analysis-- you can
have a 6.2% unemployment rate,

00:21:18.200 --> 00:21:20.397 align:middle line:84%
and that's the government
metric that's used.

00:21:20.397 --> 00:21:21.605 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I think it's higher.

00:21:21.605 --> 00:21:24.230 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: People could argue
it's far higher than that,

00:21:24.230 --> 00:21:25.860 align:middle line:90%
because people just given up.

00:21:25.860 --> 00:21:28.300 align:middle line:84%
And they've been taken
out of the statistic.

00:21:28.300 --> 00:21:31.890 align:middle line:84%
But apart from
that, if you even go

00:21:31.890 --> 00:21:34.940 align:middle line:84%
with the government
rate of 6.2%,

00:21:34.940 --> 00:21:37.530 align:middle line:90%
these are not quality jobs.

00:21:37.530 --> 00:21:39.700 align:middle line:84%
These are low income
and part-time jobs.

00:21:39.700 --> 00:21:41.950 align:middle line:84%
And with Obamacare,
what they've done

00:21:41.950 --> 00:21:44.190 align:middle line:84%
is they've given the
biggest-- I mean,

00:21:44.190 --> 00:21:47.000 align:middle line:84%
when you look at Obamacare,
and really, the good thing

00:21:47.000 --> 00:21:50.117 align:middle line:84%
about Obamacare is that if
you were sick, if I were sick,

00:21:50.117 --> 00:21:51.950 align:middle line:84%
and we couldn't get
health insurance because

00:21:51.950 --> 00:21:53.517 align:middle line:84%
of a preexisting
condition, somebody

00:21:53.517 --> 00:21:54.600 align:middle line:90%
can go out and get it now.

00:21:54.600 --> 00:21:55.900 align:middle line:90%
I have no problem with that.

00:21:55.900 --> 00:21:57.150 align:middle line:90%
I don't think anybody does.

00:21:57.150 --> 00:21:59.470 align:middle line:84%
But what I have a problem
with, with Obamacare,

00:21:59.470 --> 00:22:01.690 align:middle line:84%
and why it is a
disaster, is because it's

00:22:01.690 --> 00:22:06.990 align:middle line:84%
the biggest bailout to the
entire employer-based health

00:22:06.990 --> 00:22:09.220 align:middle line:84%
care system that we've
ever seen in this country.

00:22:09.220 --> 00:22:11.580 align:middle line:84%
As soon as that law
went into effect

00:22:11.580 --> 00:22:13.690 align:middle line:84%
and they knew that
they no longer had

00:22:13.690 --> 00:22:16.100 align:middle line:84%
to provide that insurance,
that they could force

00:22:16.100 --> 00:22:18.840 align:middle line:84%
their employees who are
working 30 hours a week

00:22:18.840 --> 00:22:21.600 align:middle line:84%
or less to go buy
Obamacare, that

00:22:21.600 --> 00:22:26.380 align:middle line:84%
came off the expense ledger
for these major corporations.

00:22:26.380 --> 00:22:27.270 align:middle line:90%
And that's not right.

00:22:27.270 --> 00:22:32.140 align:middle line:84%
The taxpayer should not be
funding these corporations out

00:22:32.140 --> 00:22:35.090 align:middle line:84%
of their obligation to provide
employer-based health care.

00:22:35.090 --> 00:22:37.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's the reason
why Obamacare either

00:22:37.790 --> 00:22:42.200 align:middle line:84%
needs to be fixed or it needs
to be trashed, because of that.

00:22:42.200 --> 00:22:46.640 align:middle line:84%
Retain the rule that you cannot
deny people health insurance

00:22:46.640 --> 00:22:50.950 align:middle line:84%
or rate them up, but do not
allow these employers to get

00:22:50.950 --> 00:22:53.326 align:middle line:84%
off the hook as far as paying
employer-based health care.

00:22:53.326 --> 00:22:54.741 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What would
have happened,

00:22:54.741 --> 00:22:56.800 align:middle line:84%
John, if we had a
system in place where

00:22:56.800 --> 00:23:01.180 align:middle line:84%
if you need a new kidney,
that the government makes sure

00:23:01.180 --> 00:23:02.350 align:middle line:90%
you get that kidney?

00:23:02.350 --> 00:23:03.860 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: Well, I
think the problem

00:23:03.860 --> 00:23:08.290 align:middle line:84%
is with government-- Obamacare
is a private sector a scenario,

00:23:08.290 --> 00:23:11.270 align:middle line:84%
where the health insurance
industry is essentially

00:23:11.270 --> 00:23:12.310 align:middle line:90%
running it and gouging.

00:23:12.310 --> 00:23:14.980 align:middle line:84%
There's no regulation on it
right now through Congress,

00:23:14.980 --> 00:23:18.430 align:middle line:84%
because Congress is in massive
gridlock, as everybody's heard.

00:23:18.430 --> 00:23:21.090 align:middle line:84%
So it means that they
can get away with a lot,

00:23:21.090 --> 00:23:24.920 align:middle line:84%
as far as raising prices
in an unprecedented way.

00:23:24.920 --> 00:23:27.370 align:middle line:84%
Their profits in the
insurance industry

00:23:27.370 --> 00:23:28.390 align:middle line:90%
have never been higher.

00:23:28.390 --> 00:23:30.450 align:middle line:90%
So they love Obamacare.

00:23:30.450 --> 00:23:33.690 align:middle line:84%
But the problem is, when you
have any kind of a government

00:23:33.690 --> 00:23:37.530 align:middle line:84%
program, just
answer, it inevitably

00:23:37.530 --> 00:23:40.260 align:middle line:84%
will fail because there's so
much cronyism, there are so

00:23:40.260 --> 00:23:43.670 align:middle line:84%
many payoffs, there's so much
insider manipulation that

00:23:43.670 --> 00:23:46.210 align:middle line:84%
goes on that I don't think
anybody would trust it.

00:23:46.210 --> 00:23:49.230 align:middle line:84%
The fact is that it goes on
that way anyway right now.

00:23:49.230 --> 00:23:53.220 align:middle line:84%
We know folks that have been
in high places who have gotten

00:23:53.220 --> 00:23:57.890 align:middle line:84%
heart transplants with
nice healthy bodies

00:23:57.890 --> 00:24:01.810 align:middle line:84%
stepped out of line and got
those transplants faster

00:24:01.810 --> 00:24:04.161 align:middle line:84%
because they were
able to pony up.

00:24:04.161 --> 00:24:05.660 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not going
to name any names,

00:24:05.660 --> 00:24:07.451 align:middle line:84%
but I think you know
who I'm talking about.

00:24:07.451 --> 00:24:10.064 align:middle line:90%
And so if you had it with the--

00:24:10.064 --> 00:24:11.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They moved to
the front of the lines.

00:24:11.980 --> 00:24:13.355 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: They
certainly are very

00:24:13.355 --> 00:24:15.720 align:middle line:84%
vociferous since their
heart transplant, too.

00:24:15.720 --> 00:24:18.100 align:middle line:84%
They talk more when
they have more oxygen,

00:24:18.100 --> 00:24:19.870 align:middle line:84%
and their hearts
are working better.

00:24:19.870 --> 00:24:24.600 align:middle line:84%
So I have no problem with
having fairness in the system.

00:24:24.600 --> 00:24:26.700 align:middle line:84%
The problem that we
have right now is,

00:24:26.700 --> 00:24:34.620 align:middle line:84%
you cannot pass the buck to
American taxpayers and take

00:24:34.620 --> 00:24:37.600 align:middle line:84%
this burden of paying
for health care off

00:24:37.600 --> 00:24:41.180 align:middle line:84%
of the employer's balance sheet
and let them stick all this

00:24:41.180 --> 00:24:42.384 align:middle line:90%
money overseas.

00:24:42.384 --> 00:24:44.300 align:middle line:84%
All this money that's
out of the country right

00:24:44.300 --> 00:24:45.883 align:middle line:84%
now, these major
employers like Apple,

00:24:45.883 --> 00:24:48.680 align:middle line:84%
and you name the biggest
corporations in the world,

00:24:48.680 --> 00:24:50.330 align:middle line:84%
they're keeping
all their trillions

00:24:50.330 --> 00:24:53.430 align:middle line:84%
of dollars of cash
out of the country.

00:24:53.430 --> 00:24:55.132 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And not
paying taxes on it.

00:24:55.132 --> 00:24:56.840 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: Well, that
goes without saying.

00:24:56.840 --> 00:25:00.707 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, you can't
stick it to the taxpayer

00:25:00.707 --> 00:25:02.290 align:middle line:84%
to pay the employer-based
health care.

00:25:02.290 --> 00:25:02.957 align:middle line:90%
That's not fair.

00:25:02.957 --> 00:25:04.206 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But they're doing it.

00:25:04.206 --> 00:25:06.190 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: Well, that's
what Obamacare-- that's

00:25:06.190 --> 00:25:08.380 align:middle line:84%
the loophole in the law
that's killing the system.

00:25:08.380 --> 00:25:10.629 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So when does it
change, a new administration?

00:25:10.629 --> 00:25:14.980 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: Well, you talk
about a new administration--

00:25:14.980 --> 00:25:21.580 align:middle line:84%
it's like the Republicans hosted
their conservative dog and pony

00:25:21.580 --> 00:25:23.470 align:middle line:84%
show over the
weekend, and you had

00:25:23.470 --> 00:25:25.990 align:middle line:84%
everybody like-- first
they thought that, well, we

00:25:25.990 --> 00:25:27.070 align:middle line:90%
should rip Obama.

00:25:27.070 --> 00:25:29.660 align:middle line:84%
And then they figured out,
well, why are we ripping him?

00:25:29.660 --> 00:25:31.240 align:middle line:90%
He's not running again.

00:25:31.240 --> 00:25:32.900 align:middle line:84%
So then they start
ripping Hillary.

00:25:32.900 --> 00:25:35.470 align:middle line:84%
And now they're talking about
things like, oh, my God,

00:25:35.470 --> 00:25:36.359 align:middle line:90%
can you imagine?

00:25:36.359 --> 00:25:38.650 align:middle line:84%
They have a foundation and
there's foreign money in it.

00:25:38.650 --> 00:25:40.490 align:middle line:84%
Foreign money-- who
are you kidding?

00:25:40.490 --> 00:25:41.580 align:middle line:84%
How much foreign
money do you think

00:25:41.580 --> 00:25:43.454 align:middle line:84%
there is in all these
presidential libraries?

00:25:43.454 --> 00:25:47.539 align:middle line:84%
H. W. Bush's, George's,
Clinton's-- where you think all

00:25:47.539 --> 00:25:49.580 align:middle line:84%
the money came from to
construct these libraries?

00:25:49.580 --> 00:25:52.740 align:middle line:84%
Where do think Obama's money--
did it come from, as we know,

00:25:52.740 --> 00:25:55.360 align:middle line:84%
cheap petro dollars
from the Middle East?

00:25:55.360 --> 00:25:56.620 align:middle line:90%
We all know this.

00:25:56.620 --> 00:26:00.600 align:middle line:84%
So the kettle calls the
pot black all the time.

00:26:00.600 --> 00:26:02.910 align:middle line:84%
The bottom line is, they're
looking for anything

00:26:02.910 --> 00:26:06.130 align:middle line:84%
they can to indict any
Democratic candidate.

00:26:06.130 --> 00:26:08.560 align:middle line:84%
And I think it
appears that there

00:26:08.560 --> 00:26:10.312 align:middle line:90%
is an anointed one coming on.

00:26:10.312 --> 00:26:11.770 align:middle line:84%
And she hasn't
announced yet, but I

00:26:11.770 --> 00:26:14.540 align:middle line:84%
think everybody is fairly
certain that Hillary Clinton,

00:26:14.540 --> 00:26:16.910 align:middle line:84%
unless she dies between
now and the election,

00:26:16.910 --> 00:26:17.824 align:middle line:90%
she's going to run.

00:26:17.824 --> 00:26:19.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I see a dark horse
popping in here, though.

00:26:19.990 --> 00:26:23.550 align:middle line:84%
Somewhere, either whether it's
a Republican or a Democrat,

00:26:23.550 --> 00:26:27.420 align:middle line:84%
