I think the menagerie that you
get with the groups out there,

00:26:50.130 --> 00:26:51.690 align:middle line:84%
I think this is
what you're getting.

00:26:51.690 --> 00:26:53.710 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Slim pickings.

00:26:53.710 --> 00:26:56.840 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: There's not much
on the Democratic side,

00:26:56.840 --> 00:26:58.310 align:middle line:90%
other than Hillary.

00:26:58.310 --> 00:27:01.720 align:middle line:84%
And there's certainly the same
familiar cast of characters

00:27:01.720 --> 00:27:03.060 align:middle line:90%
that have been running.

00:27:03.060 --> 00:27:07.386 align:middle line:84%
The dark horse would be, let's
say McCain decided that--

00:27:07.386 --> 00:27:09.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He wants to
come back and run again?

00:27:09.260 --> 00:27:09.910 align:middle line:90%
>>CURTIS: Forget my age.

00:27:09.910 --> 00:27:11.830 align:middle line:84%
What does age got to
do with it anymore?

00:27:11.830 --> 00:27:13.421 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He's done.

00:27:13.421 --> 00:27:15.420 align:middle line:84%
>>CURTIS: But you're
talking about a dark horse.

00:27:15.420 --> 00:27:19.322 align:middle line:84%
So, who do you think,
Elizabeth Warren?

00:27:19.322 --> 00:27:20.530 align:middle line:90%
She's not quite ready for it.

00:27:20.530 --> 00:27:22.964 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Scott Walker's
coming on like crazy,

00:27:22.964 --> 00:27:24.130 align:middle line:90%
the governor from Wisconsin.

00:27:24.130 --> 00:27:25.620 align:middle line:90%
>>CURTIS: He's from Wisconsin.

